[[Image:Pueblo01.png|thumb|350px|Location of '''Eight Northern Pueblos''' and neighboring pueblos in New Mexico]]
The '''Eight Northern Pueblos''' of [[New Mexico]] are [[Taos Pueblo|Taos]], [[Picuris Pueblo, New Mexico|Picuris]], [[Santa Clara Pueblo, New Mexico|Santa Clara]], [[Ohkay Owingeh Pueblo|Ohkay Owingeh]] (formerly San Juan), [[San Ildefonso Pueblo, New Mexico|San Ildefonso]], [[Nambé Pueblo|Nambé]], [[Pojoaque Pueblo|Pojoaque]], and [[Tesuque, New Mexico|Tesuque]]. 

Taos and Picuris are [[Tiwa language|Tiwa]]-speaking [[pueblo]]s; the rest speak [[Tewa language|Tewa]].  Tiwa and Tewa are closely related languages of the [[Tanoan language]] family.  These pueblos make up the ''Eight Northern Pueblos Council'', which sponsors craft fairs, advocates for the legal interests of the pueblos, etc. The Capital of the Eight Northern Pueblos is located in [[Ohkay Owingeh]]. Ohkay Owingeh was formerly known as San Juan, but changed to its original Tewa name in 2005.

